name: The Night Has a Thousand Eyes
Hyper, Hyper
comments: Story behind the song: In 1994, edel on the Club Tools label advertised the techno compilation "Hyper, Hyper". A&R man Jens Thele asked his friends/colleagues, at that time acting as Kosmos to do a track for the TV spot. This showed typos of DJ/artist names disappearing into a blue sky, parallel to the names of artists included being shouted to a simple techno beat. That made people wanting to buy the track, not the compilation, storm German record shops, which forced edel to rush release a full length version of the track. Topping the charts, this started Scooter 's success and - quoting parts from Scottish Ultra-Sonic's "Annihilating Rhythm" for the track - also marked their way to work. An extended version of the ad appears at 1:58 in the clip for the song.
